=============================
| Parameterized Constructor |
=============================
👉 A parameterized constructor is a constructor that accepts parameters to initialize an object with different values.

Without Parameterized Constructor
---------------------------------
    class Student:
    
        def __init__(self):
            self.name = "Mridul"
    
    s1 = Student()
    s2 = Student()
    
    print(s1.name) # All object same
    print(s2.name) # All object same

O/P : Mridul  
      Mridul

With Parameterized Constructor
------------------------------
    class Student:
    
        def __init__(self, name):
            self.name = name
    
    s1 = Student("Mridul")
    s2 = Student("Rahul")
    
    print(s1.name)   # All object have own value
    print(s2.name)   # All object have own value

O/P : Mridul
      Rahul

Multiple Parameters
-------------------
    class Student:
        def __init__(self, name, age, course):    
            self.name = name    
            self.age = age    
            self.course = course
    s1 = Student("Mridul", 21, "Python")
    
    print(s1.name)
    print(s1.age)
    print(s1.course)

O/P : Mridul
      21
      Python

=======================================================================
| Difference Between Normal Constructor and Parameterized Constructor |
=======================================================================
___________________________________________________________________________________
| Normal Constructor                          | Parameterized Constructor          |
| ------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| No parameters (except `self`)               | Accepts one or more parameters     |
| Same values for every object (if hardcoded) | Different values for each object   |
| Less flexible                               | More flexible                      |
| Used for default initialization             | Used for customized initialization |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=========================================
| Instance Variables vs Class Variables |
=========================================

👉 What is a instance Variable?
   An instance variable is a variable that belongs to a specific object (instance).Each object has its own copy of the 
   instance variable.

👉 What is a Class Variable?
    A class variable is a variable that belongs to the class itself. It is shared by all objects of that class.

Instance Variable
-----------------
