==================
| Methods in OOP |
==================
👉 A method is a function that is defined inside a class. It is used to perform operations on objects or classes.
👉 Method = Function inside a Class
        class Student:
            def show(self):
                print("Hello")

--------------------
| Types of Methods |
--------------------
👉 Instance Method
    An instance method works with instance variables and is called using an object. It always takes self as the first parameter.

class Bank:
    def __init__(self, balance):
        self.balance = balance

    def deposit(self, amount):
        self.balance += amount

        print(self.balance)

acc = Bank(1000)
acc.deposit(500)

O/P : 1500

👉 Class Method
    A class method works with class variables. It uses cls instead of self and is decorated with @classmethod.

class Student:
    college = "ABC College"

    @classmethod
    def show_college(cls):    cls = Current Class
        print(cls.college)

Student.show_college()

O/P : ABC College

👉 Static Method
    A static method does not use instance variables or class variables. 
    It is an independent utility method and is decorated with @staticmethod.

    class Calculator:
        @staticmethod
        def add(a, b):
            return a + b
print(Calculator.add(5, 3))

O/P : 8

-----------------
| Summary Table |
-----------------
____________________________________________________________________________________
| Feature         | Instance Method    | Class Method        | Static Method       |
| --------------- | ------------------ | ------------------- | ------------------- |
| First Parameter | `self`             | `cls`               | None                |
| Decorator       | None               | `@classmethod`      | `@staticmethod`     |
| Works With      | Instance Variables | Class Variables     | Neither             |
| Called Using    | Object             | Class (recommended) | Class (recommended) |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

----------------------
| Complete Breakdown |
----------------------
______________________________________________________________________
| Code                                 | Type                        |
| ------------------------------------ | --------------------------- |
| `college = "This Is Colz Name"`      | ✅ Class Variable          |
| `self.name = name`                   | ✅ Instance Variable       |
| `self.age = age`                     | ✅ Instance Variable       |
| `def __init__(...)`                  | ✅ Constructor             |
| `def show(self)`                     | ✅ Instance Method         |
| `@classmethod def show_college(cls)` | ✅ Class Method            |
| `s1 = Student(...)`                  | ✅ Object Creation         |
| `s1.show()`                          | ✅ Calling Instance Method |
| `Student.show_college()`             | ✅ Calling Class Method    |
