| Method Overriding |
=====================
👉 Method Overriding is the process where a child class provides its own implementation of a method that already 
    exists in the parent class.
✔️ Method name should be same
✔️ Parent and child should have inheritance

    class Animal:    
        def sound(self):
            print("Animal Sound")
    
    class Dog(Animal):    
        def sound(self):
            print("Dog Barks")
    
    d = Dog()
    d.sound()    # now child replace parent method

O/P : Dog Barks
