===============
| Abstraction |
===============
👉 Abstraction is the process of hiding implementation details and showing only the essential features to the user.

from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Animal(ABC):           # Abstract Class
    @abstractmethod          # Abstract Method
    def sound(self):
        pass
 
class Dog(Animal):           # Child Class
    def sound(self):
        print("Dog Barks")

d = Dog()
d.sound()

O/P : Dog Barks
----------------------------------------------------
# Multiple Abstract Methods

from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Shape(ABC):

    @abstractmethod
    def area(self):
        pass

    @abstractmethod
    def perimeter(self):
        pass

class Rectangle(Shape):

    def area(self):
        print("Area")

    def perimeter(self):
        print("Perimeter"


Encapsulation vs Abstraction
__________________________________________________
| Encapsulation          | Abstraction           |
| ---------------------- | --------------------- |
| Hides data             | Hides implementation  |
| Uses private variables | Uses abstract classes |
| Focus on security      | Focus on simplicity   |
--------------------------------------------------

-----------
| Summary |
-----------
______________________________________________________________
| Concept                  | Meaning                         |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |
| ABC                      | Abstract Base Class             |
| `@abstractmethod`        | Method without implementation   |
| Child Class              | Must implement abstract methods |
| Object of Abstract Class | Not Allowed                     |
| Main Purpose             | Hide implementation details     |
--------------------------------------------------------------




